Revealing the arboreal frog genus Auparoparo: A new classification after 130 years of Oreophryne sensu lato, subfamily Asterophrinae (Anura: Microhylidae)

author: "Allison Fisher, Ke Cao, Allen Allison, Bulisa Iova, and Allison Fisher, Ke Cao,

Sequence authors: Allison Fisher, Ke Cao, Marguerite Butler, Iqbal Setiadi, Ben Evans

Names explanation: 
Oreophryne senckenbergiana is the type species for the genus Oreophryne (opinion 1266, Bull. zool. Nom., vol 41, pt 1, March 1984). These sequences are collected from the O. senkenbergiana type locality. The species name was later synonymized with Oreophryne moluccensis by (Parker, H. W. 1934. A monograph of the frogs of the family microhylidae. London: Trustees of the British Museum.), based on morphological similarity which is unerliable as we show in our manuscript. O. moluccensis and O. senkenbergiana occur on a different islands separated by open ocean and are almost certainly distinct species. Cryptic species are common in this clade.

